Set up your PC and Raspberry Pi 2 or 3, or MBM 
Next, wire up the doorbell and power relay as shown below. The power relay will be used to lock and unlock the door.

https://hackster.imgix.net/uploads/image/file/104713/Raspberry%20Pi%20Sketch.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat&w=740&h=555&fit=max
https://hackster.imgix.net/uploads/image/file/104712/Minnowboard%20Max%20Sketch%20Image.png?auto=compress%2Cformat&w=740&h=555&fit=max

Now wire up the same power relay to the lock, or electric door strike, as shown below
https://hackster.imgix.net/uploads/image/file/107787/DoorStrikeDiagramCrop.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat&w=740&h=555&fit=max
https://hackster.imgix.net/uploads/image/file/107795/Power%20Relay%20Image.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat&w=740&h=555&fit=max
https://hackster.imgix.net/uploads/image/file/107794/DoorStrikeImage.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat&w=740&h=555&fit=max

Plug in your USB webcam, keyboard, and mouse into your Raspberry Pi 2 or MBM.
